{"title_page": "Shamarh Brooks", "text_new": "{{short description|West Indian cricketer}}\n{{Infobox cricketer\n| name               = Shamarh Brooks\n| full_name          = Shamarh Shaqad Joshua Brooks\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|10|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[Saint Michael, Barbados]]\n| batting            = Right-handed\n| bowling            = [[Leg spin|Legbreak]]\n| role               = Batsman\n\n| international      = true\n| country            = West Indies\n| internationalspan  = 2019\n\n| testdebutdate      = 22 August\n| testdebutyear      = 2019\n| testdebutagainst   = India\n| testcap            = 318\n| lasttestdate       = 27 November\n| lasttestyear       = 2019\n| lasttestagainst    = Afghanistan\n\n| club1              = [[Barbados national cricket team|Barbados]]\n| year1              = {{nowrap|2007\u2013present}}\n| club2              = [[St Kitts & Nevis Patriots]]\n| year2              = 2016\u20132017\n\n| columns            = 4\n\n| column1            = [[Test cricket|Test]]\n| matches1           = 3\n| runs1              = 174\n| bat avg1           = 34.80\n| 100s/50s1          = 1/1\n| top score1         = 111\n| deliveries1        = \u2013\n| wickets1           = \u2013\n| bowl avg1          = \u2013\n| fivefor1           = \u2013\n| tenfor1            = \u2013\n| best bowling1      = \u2013\n| catches/stumpings1 = 6/\u2013\n| column2            = [[First-class cricket|FC]]\n| matches2           = 76\n| runs2              = 3,879\n| bat avg2           = 34.43\n| 100s/50s2          = 6/24\n| top score2         = 166\n| deliveries2        = 791\n| wickets2           = 7\n| bowl avg2          = 78.14\n| fivefor2           = 0\n| tenfor2            = 0\n| best bowling2      = 2/68\n| catches/stumpings2 = 68/\u2013\n| column3            = [[List A cricket|LA]]\n| matches3           = 35\n| runs3              = 748\n| bat avg3           = 26.71\n| 100s/50s3          = 0/4\n| top score3         = 61[[not out|*]]\n| deliveries3        = 60\n| wickets3           = 4\n| bowl avg3          = 10.50\n| fivefor3           = 0\n| tenfor3            = 0\n| best bowling3      = 2/12\n| catches/stumpings3 = 16/\u2013\n| column4            = [[Twenty20|T20]]\n| matches4           = 34\n| runs4              = 359\n| bat avg4           = 19.94\n| 100s/50s4          = 0/1\n| top score4         = 53\n| deliveries4        = \u2013\n| wickets4           = \u2013\n| bowl avg4          = \u2013\n| fivefor4           = \u2013\n| tenfor4            = \u2013\n| best bowling4      = \u2013\n| catches/stumpings4 = 13/\u2013\n\n| source             = http://www.espncricinfo.com/westindies/content/player/230555.html ESPNcricinfo\n| date               = 27 November 2019\n}}\n'''Sharmarh Shaqad Joshua Brooks''' (born 1 October 1988) is a [[West Indian cricket team|West Indies]] cricketer who plays first-class cricket for [[Barbados national cricket team|Barbados]] and made his [[Test cricket]] debut for the West Indies in August 2019. Though successful in under-19 cricket, played for the West Indies in two World Cups, Brook struggled at first-class level and was dropped from Barbados' national team in 2012. He returned in 2015 and began to captain the [[West Indies A cricket team|West Indies A team]] in 2016.\n\n==Early career==\nBrooks was seen as a cricket prodigy in his teenage years. He played for the [[West Indies under-19 cricket team]] in the [[2006 Under-19 Cricket World Cup]], made his [[first-class cricket]] debut for [[Barbados national cricket team|Barbados]] in 2007 and captained the West Indies in the [[2008 Under-19 Cricket World Cup]].<ref name=cricprofile>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/westindies/content/player/230555.html|title=Shamarh Brooks - Check Brooks's News, Career, Age, Rankings, Stats|access-date=23 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref><ref name=bloomer>{{cite web|url=https://barbadostoday.bb/2019/08/15/late-bloomer/|title=Late bloomer|last=Harris|first=David|date=15 August 2019|access-date=23 August 2019|work=Barbados Today}}</ref> He remained in the Barbados national team for several years, but never realized his full potential and after a particularly bad year in 2012, scoring just 76 runs at an average of 8.44, he was dropped from the national team.<ref name=bloomer/>\n\nBrooks didn't play another first-class match until 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/97/97644/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by Shamarh Brooks|access-date=23 August 2019|work=CricketArchive|url-access=subscription}}</ref> but immediately upon his return he scored his maiden first-class century against the [[Windward Islands cricket team|Windward Islands]].<ref name=bloomer/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/8893/scorecard/787157/barbados-vs-windward-islands-wicb-professional-cricket-league-regional-4-day-tournament-2014-15|title=Full Scorecard of Barbados vs Windward Islands, WICB Professional Cricket League Regional 4 Day Tournament, 2nd Innings - Score Report|access-date=23 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref> Over the next five years, he scored 3091 runs at an average of 38.63, including five centuries and 20 half-centuries.<ref name=bloomer/>\n\nBrooks began to make steps towards Test cricket by captaining unofficial Test matches for the West Indies' second team, [[West Indies A cricket team|West Indies A]], from 2016. This culminated in the West Indies A series against [[India A cricket team|India A]] in England in 2018, where he scored 91 in the first match<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/cricket/news/ambris-brooks-help-west-indies-a-take-250-run-lead-against-india-a/articleshow/64875672.cms|title=West Indies A vs India A: Ambris, Brooks help West Indies A take 250-run lead against India A|date=5 July 2018|access-date=23 August 2019|work=Times of India}}</ref> and 121 [[not out]] in the second match to finish as the highest run-scorer for the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/firstcricket/sports-news/shamarh-brooks-gritty-ton-helps-west-indies-a-reach-3019-against-india-a-on-day-1-of-2nd-unofficial-test-4714351.html|title=Shamarh Brooks' gritty ton helps West Indies A reach 301/9 against India A on Day 1 of 2nd unofficial Test|date=11 July 2018|access-date=23 August 2019|work=Firstpost}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/batting/most_runs_career.html?id=12397;type=series|title=India A v West Indies A unofficial Test Series, 2018 Cricket Team Records & Stats|access-date=23 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref>\n\n==Test career==\nIn January 2019, Brooks was named in the West Indies' [[Test cricket|Test]] squad for their series [[English cricket team in the West Indies in 2018\u201319|against England]] as a reward for his first-class form,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/25769086/darren-bravo-returns-west-indies-test-squad-face-england|title=Darren Bravo returns to West Indies Test squad to face England|date=15 January 2019|access-date=15 January 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.loopjamaica.com/content/jamaican-john-campbell-called-test-duty|title=Jamaican John Campbell called up for Test duty|date=16 January 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=Loop Jamaica}}</ref> but he did not play. He then captained West Indies A in another series against India A in July and August 2019. Initially he was only meant to captain the final of three unofficial Test matches, with [[Kraigg Brathwaite]] captaining the first two,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportsmax.tv/index.php/cricket/cricket-windies/item/40111-test-hopefuls-get-to-prove-themselves-against-india-a-next-month|title=Test hopefuls to prove themselves against India 'A' next month|last=Levy|first=Leighton|date=13 June 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=SportsMax}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://barbadostoday.bb/2019/06/13/strong-windies-a-teams-named/|title=Strong Windies A teams named|date=13 June 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=Barbados Today}}</ref> but after an injury to Brathwaite he stepped in to captain the first two matches as well.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/cricketnext/news/west-indies-selectors-make-changes-to-a-squad-as-brathwaite-dowrich-injured-2243349.html|title=West Indies Selectors Make Changes To 'A' Squad as Brathwaite, Dowrich Injured|date=25 July 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=Cricket Next}}</ref> Brooks led from the front with half centuries in both of the first two matches,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/19366/report/1190804/west-indies-a-vs-india-a-1st-unofficial-test-india-a-in-west-indies-2019|title=Recent Match Report - West Indies A vs India A 1st unofficial Test 2019|date=26 July 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/firstcricket/sports-news/india-a-vs-west-indies-a-montcin-hodge-shamarh-brooks-strike-fifties-to-take-hosts-to-2435-on-day-1-of-second-unofficial-test-7094431.html|title=India A vs West Indies A: Montcin Hodge, Shamarh Brooks strike fifties to take hosts to 243/5 on Day 1 of second unofficial Test|date=1 August 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=First Post}}</ref> He was then again named in the West Indies' Test squad, this time for their [[Indian cricket team in the West Indies and the United States in 2019|series against India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/story/1197123.html|title=Rahkeem Cornwall makes it to West Indies Test squad|date=10 August 2019|access-date=10 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.crictracker.com/uncapped-rahkeem-cornwall-shamarh-brooks-in-windies-squad-for-india-test-series/|title=Uncapped Rahkeem Cornwall, Shamarh Brooks in Windies squad for India Test series|author=Bijoy|date=10 August 2019|access-date=24 August 2019|work=CricTracker}}</ref>\n\nHe made his Test debut for the West Indies against [[India national cricket team|India]] on 22 August 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1188628.html |title=1st Test, ICC World Test Championship at North Sound, Aug 22-26 2019 |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=22 August 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, in the one-off Test [[West Indian cricket team against Afghanistan in India in 2019\u201320|against Afghanistan]], Brooks scored his first century in Test cricket, with 111 runs.<ref name=\"CB\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cricbuzz.com/cricket-news/111037/shamarh-brooks-maiden-ton-inflates-lead-to-90 |title=Shamarh Brooks' maiden ton inflates lead to 90 |work=CricBuzz |accessdate=28 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Twenty20 franchise cricket==\nBrooks played for the [[St Kitts & Nevis Patriots]] in the [[Caribbean Premier League]], the top-level Twenty20 league in the West Indies, for two seasons in [[2016 Caribbean Premier League|2016]] and [[2017 Caribbean Premier League|2017]]. He played 4 matches in each season, and across them both scored 119 runs at an average of 23.80 with a strike-rate of 120.20.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/caribbean-premier-league-2016/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=11003;team=5543;type=tournament|title=Caribbean Premier League, 2016 - St Kitts and Nevis Patriots Cricket Team Records & Stats|access-date=24 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/caribbean-premier-league-2017/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=11754;team=5543;type=tournament|title=Caribbean Premier League, 2017 - St Kitts and Nevis Patriots Cricket Team Records & Stats|access-date=24 August 2019|work=ESPncricinfo}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cricinfo}}\n\n{{St Kitts and Nevis Patriots Squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brooks, Sharmarh}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:West Indies Test cricketers]]\n[[Category:Barbadian cricketers]]\n[[Category:Barbados cricketers]]\n[[Category:People from Saint Michael, Barbados]]\n[[Category:St Kitts and Nevis Patriots cricketers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|West Indian cricketer}}\n{{Infobox cricketer\n| name               = Shamarh Brooks\n| full_name          = Shamarh Shaqad Joshua Brooks\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1988|10|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[Saint Michael, Barbados]]\n| batting            = Right-handed\n| bowling            = [[Leg spin|Legbreak]]\n| role               = Batsman\n\n| international      = true\n| country            = West Indies\n| internationalspan  = 2019\n\n| testdebutdate      = 22 August\n| testdebutyear      = 2019\n| testdebutagainst   = India\n| testcap            = 318\n| lasttestdate       = 27 November\n| lasttestyear       = 2019\n| lasttestagainst    = Afghanistan\n\n| club1              = [[Barbados national cricket team|Barbados]]\n| year1              = {{nowrap|2007\u2013present}}\n| club2              = [[St Kitts & Nevis Patriots]]\n| year2              = 2016\u20132017\n\n| columns            = 4\n\n| column1            = [[Test cricket|Test]]\n| matches1           = 3\n| runs1              = 174\n| bat avg1           = 34.80\n| 100s/50s1          = 1/1\n| top score1         = 111\n| deliveries1        = \u2013\n| wickets1           = \u2013\n| bowl avg1          = \u2013\n| fivefor1           = \u2013\n| tenfor1            = \u2013\n| best bowling1      = \u2013\n| catches/stumpings1 = 6/\u2013\n| column2            = [[First-class cricket|FC]]\n| matches2           = 76\n| runs2              = 3,879\n| bat avg2           = 34.43\n| 100s/50s2          = 6/24\n| top score2         = 166\n| deliveries2        = 791\n| wickets2           = 7\n| bowl avg2          = 78.14\n| fivefor2           = 0\n| tenfor2            = 0\n| best bowling2      = 2/68\n| catches/stumpings2 = 68/\u2013\n| column3            = [[List A cricket|LA]]\n| matche