icinfo}}</ref><ref name=bloomer>{{cite web|url=https://barbadostoday.bb/2019/08/15/late-bloomer/|title=Late bloomer|last=Harris|first=David|date=15 August 2019|access-date=23 August 2019|work=Barbados Today}}</ref> He remained in the Barbados national team for several years, but never realized his full potential and after a particularly bad year in 2012, scoring just 76 runs at an average of 8.44, he was dropped from the national team.<ref name=bloomer/>\n\nBrooks didn't play another first-class match until 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/97/97644/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by Sharmarh Brooks|access-date=23 August 2019|work=CricketArchive|url-access=subscription}}</ref> but immediately upon his return he scored his maiden first-class century against the [[Windward Islands cricket team|Windward Islands]].<ref name=bloomer/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/8893/scorecard/787157/barbados-vs-windward-islands-wicb-professional-cricket-league-regional-4-day-tournament-2014-15|title=Full Scorecard of Barbados vs Windward Islands, WICB Professional Cricket League Regional 4 Day Tournament, 2nd Innings - Score Report|access-date=23 August 2019|work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref> Over the next five years, he scored 3091 runs at an average of 38.63, including five centuries and 20 half-centuries.<ref name=bloomer/>\n\nBrooks began to make steps towards Test cricket by captaining unofficial Test matches for the West Indies' second team, [[West Indies A cricket team|West Indies A]], from 2016. This culminated in the West Indies A series against [[India A cricket team|India A]] in England in 2018, where he scored 91 in the first match<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/cricket/news/ambris-brooks-help-west-indies-a-take-250-run-lead-against-india-a/articleshow/64875672.cms|title=West Indies A vs India A: Ambris, Brooks help West Indies A take 250-run lead against India A|date