{"title_page": "Slobodan Kova\u010d", "text_new": "{{Infobox volleyball player\n| name             = Slobodan Kova\u010d\n| image            = Slobodan Kova\u010d - Sir Safety Umbria Volley 2013-2014.jpg\n| image_size       = 200px\n| fullname         = \n| nickname         = \n| nationality      = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia]]n\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1967|9|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[Veliko Gradi\u0161te]], [[Socialist Republic of Serbia|Serbia]],<br>[[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]]\n| position         = Outside hitter\n| height           = 2.00 m\n| weight           = \n| spike            = \n| block            = \n| team             = \n| currentnumber    =\n| nationalteam     = \n| nationalyears    = \n| currentcoachteam = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbia]]\n| coachyears       = 2008\u20132010<br>2010\u20132014<br>2014\u20132015<br>2015\u20132016<br>2016\u20132018<br>2017\u20132018<br>2018\u20132019<br>2019\u2013<br>2019\u20132020\n| coachteams       = {{flagicon|SRB}} [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sir Volley|Sir Safety Perugia]]<br> {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Sir Volley|Sir Safety Perugia]]<br> {{flagicon|TUR}} [[Halkbank Ankara]]<br> {{flagicon|SLO}} [[Slovenia men's national volleyball team|Slovenia]]<br> {{flagicon|RUS}} [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]<ref>[https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/Russia/98652/rus-m-slobodan-kovac-appointed-belogorie-coach.html ''RUS M: Slobodan Kova\u010d appointed Belogorie coach!''] \u2013 worldofvolley.com \u2013 22.05.2018</ref><br> {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbia]]<br> {{flagicon|POL}} [[Jastrz\u0119bski W\u0119giel]] \n| years            = 1983\u20131985<br>1985\u20131988<br>1988\u20131992<br>1992\u20131993<br>1993\u20131994<br>1994\u20131995<br>1995\u20131999<br>1999\u20132002<br>2002\u20132003<br>2003\u20132004<br>2003\u20132004<br>2004\u20132006<br>2006\u20132007\n| clubs            = {{flagicon|YUG}} VGSK Veliko Gradi\u0161te<br> {{flagicon|YUG}} Kolubara<br> {{flagicon|YUG}} [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina Novi Sad]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} Volley Gioia<br> {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Aris Thessaloniki Volleyball Club|Aris Thessaloniki]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} Volley Gioia<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Volley Lube]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Prisma Volley|Magna Grecia Volley]]<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} Pallavolo Agnone<br> {{flagicon|FRA}} GFC Ajaccio VB<br> {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Pallavolo Molfetta]]<br> {{flagicon|IRN}} [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]<br> {{flagicon|SRB}} [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n| medaltemplates   =\n{{MedalCountry|{{FR-YUG}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[volleyball]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Volleyball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]]|[[Volleyball at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Team]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[1996 Summer Olympics|1996 Atlanta]]|[[Volleyball at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Team]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Men's European Volleyball Championship|European Championship]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1997 Men's European Volleyball Championship|1997 Netherlands]]|}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[1995 Men's European Volleyball Championship|1995 Greece]]|}}\n{{MedalCountry|{{YUG}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Mediterranean Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1991 Mediterranean Games|1991 Athens]]|[[Volleyball at the 1991 Mediterranean Games|Team]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Slobodan Kova\u010d''' (born 13 September 1967) is a former [[Serbia]]n [[volleyball]] player and coach, a head coach of the [[Serbia men's national volleyball team]]. \n\n==Career==\nIn 2014, he was appointed as a head coach of the [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran men's national team]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=44443&Language=en#.U9BS-vmSySo ''Slobodan Kovac new coach of Iran men\u2019s national team''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 13.03.2014</ref> until the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>[http://theiranproject.com/blog/2014/03/19/slobodan-kovac-has-incentive-to-coach-iran-volleyball-team/ ''Slobodan Kovac has incentive to coach Iran volleyball team''] \u2013 theiranproject.com \u2013 19.03.2014</ref> Previously competing for [[Yugoslavia]], he won team medals at the [[Atlanta]] [[1996 Olympics]] (bronze) and his inaugural gold medal at the [[Sydney]] [[2000 Summer Olympics]] at the age of 33.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ko/slobodan-kovac-1.html}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010-2014 and 2015-2016, he was a head coach of [[Sir Safety Perugia]], reaching the Superlega finals twice, Italy's top tier league. Kova\u010d in 2016 officially became a new head coach of Halkbank Ankara.<ref>[https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/Turkey/78856/transfer-bomb-in-2017-perugias-coach-on-the-bench-of-halkbank.html ''TRANSFER BOMB IN 2017: Perugia\u2019s coach on the bench of Halkbank''] \u2013 worldofvolley.com \u2013 02.01.2017</ref> In the same year he was elected as a head coach of the [[Slovenia men's national volleyball team|Slovenia men's national team]].<ref>[https://www.sta.si/2381248/slobodan-kovac-objavil-sirsi-seznam-reprezentantov ''Slobodan Kova\u010d objavil \u0161ir\u0161i seznam reprezentantov''] \u2013 sta.si \u2013 26.04.2017</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n[[File:2014 Volleyball World League, Italy vs Iran (31 May 2014)-13.jpg|260px|thumb|At [[2014 FIVB Volleyball World League|2014 Volleyball World League]]]]\n\n===As a player===\n* '''[[CEV Challenge Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] 1997/1998 \u2013 with [[Volley Lube]]\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''1988/1989''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Championship, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1991/1992''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Cup, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1991/1992''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Championship, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1993/1994''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Greek Championship, with [[Aris Thessaloniki Volleyball Club|Aris Thessaloniki]]\n** '''2004/2005''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Iranian Championship, with [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]\n** '''2005/2006''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Iranian Championship, with [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Serbian Championship, with [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n* '''National team'''\n** '''1991''' [[File:Silver MedGames.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 1991 Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games]]\n** '''1995''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1995 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''1996''' [[File:Bronze medal olympic.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]]\n** '''1997''' [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1997 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2000''' [[File:Gold medal olympic.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]]\n\n===As a coach===\n\n* '''[[CEV Challenge Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 CEV Challenge Cup|2018/2019]] \u2013 with [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]<ref>[https://sport.blic.rs/ostali-sportovi/odbojka/prvi-put-u-istoriji-slobodan-kovac-i-nemanja-petric-pobednici-kupa-izazivaca-sa/g0f3wgv ''PRVI PUT U ISTORIJI Slobodan Kova\u010d i Nemanja Petri\u0107 pobednici Kupa Izaziva\u010da sa Belogorjem''] \u2013 sport.blic.rs \u2013 28.03.2019</ref>\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2008/2009''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Serbian Championship, with [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n** '''2009/2010''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Serbian Championship, with [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Italian Championship, with [[Sir Volley|Sir Safety Perugia]]\n** '''2015/2016''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Italian Championship, with [[Sir Volley|Sir Safety Perugia]]\n** '''2016/2017''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Turkish Championship, with [[Halkbank Ankara]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Turkish Cup, with [[Halkbank Ankara]]\n** '''2017/2018''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Turkish Championship, with [[Halkbank Ankara]]\n* '''National teams'''\n** '''2014''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men|Asian Games]], with [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran]] \n** '''2019''' [[File:Gold medal europe.svg|16px]] [[2019 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]], with [[Serbia men's national volleyball team|Serbia]]<ref>[https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/CEV/106233/parisian-dream-comes-true-serbia-conquer-eurovolley-for-3rd-time.html ''Parisian dream comes true: Serbia conquer EuroVolley for 3rd time!''] \u2013 worldofvolley \u2013 29.09.2019</ref>\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2008:''' \u2013 Coach of the Year in [[Serbia]]\n* '''2009:''' \u2013 Coach of the Year in [[Serbia]]\n* '''2010:''' \u2013 Coach of the Year in [[Serbia]]\n* '''2013:''' \u2013 Coach of the Year in [[Italy]]\n* '''2014:''' \u2013 Coach of the Year in [[Italy]]<ref>[https://ww1.legavolley.it/?p=110939 ''Comunicato Stampa della Lega Pallavolo Serie A''] \u2013 02.10.2014</ref>\n* '''2019:''' \u2013 CEV Men\u2019s Volleyball Team Coach of the Year<ref>[https://www.cev.eu/News.aspx?NewsID=29899 ''Top achievements honoured at European Volleyball Gala''] \u2013 cev.eu \u2013 25.10.2019</ref>\n* '''2019:''' \u2013 [[Awards of Olympic Committee of Serbia|Coach of the Year]] by the [[Olympic Committee of Serbia]]\n\n==See also==\n*[