bia]]n [[volleyball]] player and coach, a head coach of the [[Serbia men's national volleyball team]]. \n\n==Career==\nIn 2014, he was appointed as a head coach of the [[Iran men's national volleyball team|Iran men's national team]]<ref>[http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=44443&Language=en#.U9BS-vmSySo ''Slobodan Kovac new coach of Iran men\u2019s national team''] \u2013 fivb.org \u2013 13.03.2014</ref> until the [[2016 Summer Olympics]].<ref>[http://theiranproject.com/blog/2014/03/19/slobodan-kovac-has-incentive-to-coach-iran-volleyball-team/ ''Slobodan Kovac has incentive to coach Iran volleyball team''] \u2013 theiranproject.com \u2013 19.03.2014</ref> Previously competing for [[Yugoslavia]], he won team medals at the [[Atlanta]] [[1996 Olympics]] (bronze) and his inaugural gold medal at the [[Sydney]] [[2000 Summer Olympics]] at the age of 33.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ko/slobodan-kovac-1.html}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010-2014 and 2015-2016, he was a head coach of [[Sir Safety Perugia]], reaching the Superlega finals twice, Italy's top tier league. Kova\u010d in 2016 officially became a new head coach of Halkbank Ankara.<ref>[https://www.worldofvolley.com/Latest_news/Turkey/78856/transfer-bomb-in-2017-perugias-coach-on-the-bench-of-halkbank.html ''TRANSFER BOMB IN 2017: Perugia\u2019s coach on the bench of Halkbank''] \u2013 worldofvolley.com \u2013 02.01.2017</ref> In the same year he was elected as a head coach of the [[Slovenia men's national volleyball team|Slovenia men's national team]].<ref>[https://www.sta.si/2381248/slobodan-kovac-objavil-sirsi-seznam-reprezentantov ''Slobodan Kova\u010d objavil \u0161ir\u0161i seznam reprezentantov''] \u2013 sta.si \u2013 26.04.2017</ref>\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n[[File:2014 Volleyball World League, Italy vs Iran (31 May 2014)-13.jpg|260px|thumb|At [[2014 FIVB Volleyball World League|2014 Volleyball World League]]]]\n\n===As a player===\n* '''[[CEV Challenge Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple bronze cup.svg|16px]] 1997/1998 \u2013 with [[Volley Lube]]\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''1988/1989''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Championship, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1991/1992''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Cup, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1991/1992''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Yugoslavian Championship, with [[OK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]]\n** '''1993/1994''' [[File:Silver medal with cup.svg|16px]] Greek Championship, with [[Aris Thessaloniki Volleyball Club|Aris Thessaloniki]]\n** '''2004/2005''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Iranian Championship, with [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]\n** '''2005/2006''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Iranian Championship, with [[Shahrdari Urmia VC|Shahrdari Urmia]]\n** '''2006/2007''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] Serbian Championship, with [[OK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki Kragujevac]]\n* '''National team'''\n** '''1991''' [[File:Silver MedGames.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 1991 Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games]]\n** '''1995''' [[File:Bronze medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1995 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''1996''' [[File:Bronze medal olympic.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]]\n** '''1997''' [[File:Silver medal europe.svg|16px]] [[1997 Men's European Volleyball Championship|CEV European Championship]]\n** '''2000''' [[File:Gold medal olympic.svg|16px]] [[Volleyball at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|Olympic Games]]\n\n===As a coach===\n\n* '''[[CEV Challenge Cup]]'''\n** [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018\u201319 CEV Challenge Cup|2018/2019]] \u2013 with [[VC Belogorie|Belogorie Belgorod]]<ref>[https://sport.blic.rs/ostali-sportovi/odbojka/prvi-put-u-istoriji-slobodan-kovac-i-nemanja-petric-pobednici-kupa-izazivaca-sa/g0f3wgv ''PRVI PUT U ISTORIJI Slobodan 